                     <interp inst="t18120916-157-victim1304" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 10th of September I was coming from a friend's house. I had my shawl taken from me. Who took it from me, I do not know</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18120916-157-person1305">
                  JOHN 
                  LISLE
               <interp inst="t18120916-157-person1305" type="surname" value="LISLE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120916-157-person1305" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120916-157-person1305" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 16th of September, between one and two in the morning, I was passing Mrs. Nicholl. I saw five or six men coming upon her; I put my hands out to keep them off. This was in <placeName id="t18120916-157-crimeloc858">Kingsland-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18120916-157-crimeloc858" type="placeName" value="Kingsland-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18120916-157-crimeloc858" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18120916-157-off855 t18120916-157-crimeloc858"></join>, in Edmonton-fair time. I saw the prisoner take her shawl off. Mrs. Nicoll said: he has taken my shawl. I instantly took him. This is the shawl.</p>
               <p>Prosecutrix. It is my shawl.</p>
               <p>The prisoner said nothing in his defence; called four witnesses, who gave him a good character.</p>
               <p>
